==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Winter-ground
<hw>Win"ter-ground`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <def>To coved
over in the season of winter, as for protection or shelter; <as>as, to
<ex>winter-ground</ex> the roods of a plant</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The ruddock would . . . bring thee all this,⟦br⟧
Yea, and furred moss besides, when flowers are none⟦br⟧
To <qex>winter-ground</qex> thy corse.</q> <rj><qau>Shak.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Winterkill</ent>⟦br⟧
